 industry and how does that play into gerbers planspiergallini our mission for the total company is in the feeding caring and clothing children from zero to about  years of age we want to dominate that category with gerber productsthe trends in our business are driven by birth rates the birth rate nationally is up about  percent about  million births a year give or take a fewwe entered the babyformula business about  months ago that came about because of our mission and that starts with the formula we believe breastfeeding is the best way to take care of babies but if you cant breast feed or in some cases women supplement breastfeeding we want you to try gerbera trend that negatively affected us is the early substitution of table foods when mom decides the kid should eat mashed potatoes and spaghettios but none of those foods are formulated for that age group research tells us mother uses that because its convenient but it has high sodium high fat and a lot of sugarso what were doing is trying to extend the consumption cycle by developing a toddler transitional food category  gerber graduates this would carry us from the monthold up to about  months we recently started rolling out the main meals  the first element in that toddler category were hopeful that by the end of this fiscal year well have a whole series under the gerber graduates name that might include snacks side dishes and juicestheres a big amount of consumption beyond  months that were not really taking advantage of now because when mothers give up baby food they give up usq how has the shift in environmental awareness affected gerberpiergallini the nutrition and environmental consciousness is all in our favor the trend in the us is going back to cloth diapers because of the environmental push we are the largest cloth diaper manufacturer in the united states the issue we are facing now is strong imports and they are tough to fight because of the price is so much lower  we make all of our diapers domesticallyweve got a great new diaper we just developed called the easy one for newborns its with velcro straps no pins were testing it in a number of hospitals but one thing we will never be able to beat in disposables  and they are a good product  is convenienceq is there a problem with marketing cloth diapers since the women having babies now probably have never used cloth diapers before and dont know howpiergallini most people dont know how to use cloth diapers theyd like to but they think its going to be really difficult and it isnt thats why weve recently come out with a diaper kit  two dozen diapers pins diaper liners vinyl pants diaper cover and a video tapethe tape shows how to take care of the baby but the whole idea was heres how you use cloth diapers heres how you fold them heres how you put them on the kid it even gives you the different folds for the girl and boy it costs about  but you go home open it up and you can do itq more and more companies are looking beyond us borders to global markets what is gerber doing to go beyond    next morejoan crawfords daughter wins suit against sistertonsil cancer is dangerous but treatable if caught earlyschers wife pleads guilty gets probationhigh school football not the attendance giant it used to bethe morning call sports calendarslaying suspect married victim devon guzmans father said she wed her lover michelle hetzel who is held in her death related articlesbabys food had glassdecember  gerber doll could be worth about the price of a few jars ofapril  ceo tells student athletes study hard  gerber chief oncenovember  carbon residents discover gerber settlement is hoax  bogusoctober  the end of the sun rubber storyapril  index by keywordindex by dateprivacy policyterms of serviceplease note the greenlined linked article text has been applied commercially without any involvement from our newsroom editors reporters or any other editorial staff alfred a piergallini  executive bio compensation history and contacts  equil