kets economy energy media technology personal tech entrepreneurship your money new gerber president called sound manager by paul c judge special to the new york times published january   detroit jan — alfred a piergallini today was named president and chief executive of the gerber products company succeeding david w johnson who will take the top posts at the campbell soup company mr piergallini who had been chief operating officer has been with the babyfood concern for only nine months yet his relative inexperience is hardly a drawback at gerber where a thorough restructuring by the departing chief executive mr johnson changed the corporate culture and turned the company around in two years unlike his predecessor mr piergallini is largely unknown outside the company but has built a solid reputation managing gerbers operations thats what gerber needs right now a strong operations guy said kurt a feuerman an analyst with drexel burnham lambert renewed focus on baby food mr piergallini who is  years old inherits a company that is prospering a renewed focus on baby food pushed earnings up  percent to  million in the first six months of the  fiscal year analysts say gerber is on track to earn about  a share when its fiscal year ends in march compared with  last year mr piergallini joined gerber based in fremont mich after working for a variety of consumerproducts concerns most recently he was senior vice president of the carnation company he came to mr johnsons attention after expanding carnations market share in pet food when he was hired at gerber in april those familiar with the company expected him to succeed mr johnson eventually but the change in leadership came sooner than some had expected despite rumors that mr johnson was considering an offer from campbell mr piergallini who said his management philosophy is identical to mr johnsons will not tinker with the profit machine that mr johnson has created at gerber instead he emphasized his plans to follow through on the divestitures that began under mr johnson and said he hoped to squeeze even more profit from the baby food business through wider distribution and some new food products including a line of milkbased baby formula criticism of advertisements the american academy of pediatricians has criticized gerber for aiming at consumers rather than doctors with advertisements for its new line of baby formula which became available last summer the pediatricians have said gerbers advertising campaign undermines their efforts to encourage breastfeeding mr piergallini said the opposition to the marketing strategy has not appeared to adversely affect the introduction of our formula product the company is under pressure to establish its milkbased formula which is manufactured by the bristolmyers squibb company and sold by gerber under a joint agreement gerber tried to enter the market in  with a formula called modilac but it was discontinued in  the company expects profits from its new formula to be about  million to  million annually by  to accomplish that gerber will have to raise the price of the formula by  to  percent each year said william maguire an analyst for merrill lynch sale of daycare centers mr piergallini said his first job was to complete the sale of a national chain of daycare centers which he acknowledges will not realize any significant gain for gerber he also intends to follow through on the companys plans announced in november to close a baby food plant in niagara falls ontario some wall street analysts have alerted investors to sell their gerber shares believing that the company can go no higher without mr johnson as its guide but other analysts familiar with the company suggested that gerber still had potential to grow the simple fact that al piergallini is in charge does not reduce gerbers earnings mr maguire said gerber stock fell  cents yesterday to  in trading on the new york stock exchange photo alfred a piergallini the new president and chief executive 